The `sorry` is in the line `have hp‚āÄ : p ‚Č† 0 := sorry`. This line is within the proof of `cLpNorm_mul_le`.
The goal at this point is `p ‚Č† 0`.
The context includes `hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r`.
`ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r` means that `p`, `q`, and `r` satisfy the H√∂lder triple condition, i.e., `1/p + 1/q = 1/r` (in the real number sense, not the `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě` sense).
From `1/p + 1/q = 1/r`, we can deduce that `p`, `q`, and `r` are all non-zero. Specifically, if `p = 0`, then `1/p` would be undefined (or `‚ąě` in `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě`), so the equation `1/p + 1/q = 1/r` cannot hold if `p = 0`. The same applies to `q = 0` and `r = 0`.

