```

Actually, the contradiction is simpler. If `p = 0`, then `1/p` is `‚ąě` in `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě`.
The equation `1/p + 1/q = 1/r` becomes `‚ąě + 1/q = 1/r`.
In `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě`, `‚ąě + x = ‚ąě` for any `x ‚Č† ‚ąě`.
So `‚ąě + 1/q = ‚ąě`.
Thus `‚ąě = 1/r`.
But `1/r` is finite because `r ‚Č† 0` (from `hr‚āÄ`). This is a contradiction.

So the proof would be:
```tactics
have hp‚āÄ : p ‚Č† 0 := by
  by_contra h
  have hp1 : p = 0 := h
  rw [hp1] at hpqr
  -- hpqr is now ENNReal.HolderTriple (0 : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) q r
  -- This implies 1/0 + 1/q = 1/r in ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě
  -- In Lean's `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě`, 1/0 = ‚ąě, so ‚ąě + 1/q = 1/r
  -- This is impossible because 1/r is finite (since r ‚Č† 0 by hr‚āÄ)
  -- We need to formalize this contradiction.
